Title: Malaysia
Description: Malaysia is a federation of 13 states and three federal territories. These are divided between two regions, with 11 states and two federal territories on Peninsular Malaysia and the other two states and one federal territory in East Malaysia. Each state is divided into districts, which are then divided into mukim. In Sabah and Sarawak, districts are grouped into divisions

Title: MALAYSIA
Description: A python sits on a road after swallowing a pregnant ewe in the village of Kampung Jabor, about 200 km (124 miles) east of Kuala Lumpur, on September 5, 2006. The six-metre reptile weighing 90 kg (198.5 lbs) was too laden to move, making it easy for firemen to capture it, said a local daily newspaper. Picture taken September 5, 2006. MALAYSIA OUT  NO ARCHIVE  NO SALES  REUTERS/Stringer (MALAYSIA)

Title: Malaysia
Description: ماليزيا هي -في اعتقادي- أكبر مثال على ان الإصرار و المثابرة و التمسك بالدين اهي أهم سبل النجاح، هذي الدولة الاسلامية اللي أفتخر بها شخصيا كمسلم قدرت انها تنتشل نفسها من الحضيض و تبني حاضرها المتألق خلال عشرين سنة فقط بالرغم انه الظروف اللي بدت فيها كانت صعبة للغاية، و هذا التطور بناه أشخاص عاديين مثلي و مثلك بس الفرق انهم عقدوا العزم على انهم يرفعون اسم بلادهم فوق ..... بالعمل مب بالكلام فهل يا ترى بنتعلم منهم و الا بنكتفي بالمشاهدة .... حاب أسمع رايكم i forgot to say that this fantastic photo was taken and edited by the creative and professional photographer and friend place light .... thanks dear ....

Title: MALAYSIA/
Description: Malaysian Muslim children perform morning exercise at their preschool in Putrajaya, outside Kuala Lumpur, September 12, 2007. Muslims in Malaysia begin the fasting month of Ramadan on Thursday, by fasting from dawn to sunset and are forbidden from smoking, having sexual relations, lying, breaking promises or cheating. It is to remind them of the plight of the poor and to cleanse themselves by exercising abstinence and self-control. Muslims celebrate the end of sacred Ramadan with the Eid al-Fitr festival. REUTERS/Bazuki Muhammad (MALAYSIA)
